      "span_text": "Since it is well established that trypomastigotes interact with ECM elements through members of the gp85 GPI-anchored surface glycoprotein family, as Tc85 or gp83 [CITATION_1] , it is tempting to hypothesize that adhesion of gp85 proteins to laminin or fibronectin may trigger signal transduction."
